subSubSection.paragraph:
Renopericardium indistinct from pericardium on preserved specimens. One long pair of posterior dorsal vessels running length of body (
Fig. 22
). Numerous lateral vessels emerging from each main vessel; side vessels running up side of parapodium, most unbranched but a few forking once or twice.

